{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015BLJyty4hDEL8ob7stJEEP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n\n**Root cause:** `rabbitmq-2` has a different Erlang cookie (`driftedcookie`) than `rabbitmq-0` and `rabbitmq-1` (`supersecretcookie`). This was intentionally set in the secret to simulate a maintenance failure. Since Erlang nodes require the same cookie to communicate, `rabbitmq-2` started a standalone cluster instead of joining the existing one.\n\n**Fix plan:**\n1. Patch the `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` secret to set `rabbitmq-2`'s cookie to `supersecretcookie` (same as the other nodes).\n2. Delete the `rabbitmq-2` pod so it restarts with the corrected cookie from the init container.\n3. Since `rabbitmq-2` already has Mnesia data from running standalone, I'll need to reset it and rejoin the cluster using `rabbitmqctl` commands to discard the standalone data and integrate it back into the cluster.\n\nThough I'm realizing peer discovery is configured with `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k`, so I should check if that handles the rejoin automatically or if manual intervention is needed. The `erlang-cookie` volume is ephemeral, so it'll get regenerated from the updated secret when the pod restarts, but the `data` volume is persistent—meaning the Mnesia data stays put. That's why I need to actually reset the node's data after fixing the cookie, so it can rejoin the cluster fresh instead of staying standalone. The plan is solid: patch the secret, delete the pod, wait for it to come back up, then manually reset and rejoin it to the cluster.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1461,"cache_read_input_tokens":36840,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1461},"output_tokens":17,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e25624df-e95f-44d1-a1ff-2e7ab7d85c5b","uuid":"4edb73a7-35c5-48a5-a804-45a612c14b29","request_id":"req_011CcLB3w1fiaaggTVuCm1KE"}
